thread.title_full: Wednesday on TV: Real Salt Lake faces yet another must-win game | The Salt Lake Tribune

author: Scott D. Pierce
title: Wednesday on TV: Real Salt Lake faces yet another must-win game
text:
Real Salt Lake can remain alive in the race for a Major League Soccer playoff berth … or not.
RSL hosts Portland (7:30 p.m., KMYU), and a win will keep those hopes alive. It won't guarantee the Claret-and-Cobalt a spot in the postseason, but it will leave the door open a crack.
A loss, however, will be a death knell.
Elsewhere on TV ...
Baseball playoffs: Texas Rangers at Toronto Blue Jays (2 p.m., FS1); Houston Astros at Kansas City Royals (6 p.m., FS1)
"Survivor Cambodia: Second Chance" (7 p.m., CBS/Ch. 2): Three castaways leave it all on the beach in a gut-wrenching challenge; two castaways plead for their lives in the game at a heated tribal council.
 "The Middle" (7 p.m., ABC/Ch. 4): Sue is living in her car to avoid her horrible roommate.
"The Mysteries of Laura" (7 p.m., NBC/Ch. 5): Two inmates flee prison, and one of the fugitives is Laura's old captain.
"Nature" (7 p.m., PBS/Ch. 7): The discovery in Botswana of two dead bull elephants with their ivory tusks intact—which means they died of natural causes and not from poachers—leads wildlife filmmakers Dereck and Beverly Joubert to re-create the lives the animals would have led.
"Rosewood" (7 p.m., Fox/Ch. 13): Rosewood and Villa suspect a doctor killed two of his patients.
High school football (7 p.m., Ch. 14): Roy at Northridge
"Arrow" (7 p.m., CW/Ch. 30): When an old family friend tells Oliver and Thea hat she is going to run for mayor, they are alarmed — the last three mayors were murdered.
"The Goldbergs" (7:30 p.m., ABC/Ch. 4): Adam is desperate to get out of swimming in gym class; Erica starts a club at school and, to her dismay, Barry joins.
"Criminal Minds" (8 p.m., CBS/Ch. 2): When brides-to-be in are killed on the eve of their weddings, the BAU suspects a jilted UnSub is at work.
"Modern Family" (8 p.m., ABC/Ch. 4): Cameron gets overly friendly with the fraternity guys who are renting the apartment upstairs.
"Law & Order: Special Victims Unit" (8 p.m., NBC/Ch. 5): An unarmed black man is shot and killed by three police officers.
"Nova" (8 p.m., PBS/Ch. 7): An examination of the dangers of cyber warfare.
"Empire" (8 p.m., Fox/Ch. 13): The battlng Lyons decide to shoot a music video that will capitalize on Hakeem and Jamal's duet.
